  "title": "Cook / Prep Cook / Line Cook for Turkish Cuisine",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements:</strong></p><p>Singaporean / Singapore PR / LTVP holders only!</p><p><br /><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p><br /></p><ul><li>Report to Executive Chef</li><li>In charge of managing daily operations, restocking and mise en place</li><li>Food preparation</li><li>Verify that prepared food meets requirements</li><li>Ensure quality control and presentation of the food</li><li>Adhere to safety procedures</li><li>Ensuring proper handling and storage of all food items in accordance with the standards and sanitation regulations</li><li>Handle equipment, appliances, supplies, and tools</li><li>Prepare and cook customer’s food orders</li><li>Preparing hot and cold dishes and executing requests based on required specifications</li><li>Maintain cleanliness and hygiene of the kitchen</li><li>Understanding and complying with the mandatory hygiene standards and requirements</li><li>Work with the kitchen in charge of ordering</li><li>Assist in cleaning duties</li><li>Assist in plating up meals as assigned</li><li>Helps to cook & provide staff meal</li><li>Maintain basic kitchen hygiene as well as personal hygiene.</li><li>Conduct daily housekeeping to ensure that the kitchen area is neat, tidy and clean</li><li>Perform any other duties assigned by Executive Chef</li></ul><p>Job Requirements:</p><p><br /></p><ul><li>With minimum of 1 year of relevant experience</li><li>Must be able to communicate well with team members</li><li>Physically and mentally fit and able to work in a fast-paced and demanding environment</li><li>Food safety and hygiene practice in food handling</li><li>Willing to work shifts, weekends, and public holidays</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><p>* 5 working days</p><p>* Staff meals provided</p><p>* Staff discount at Pera</p><p>* Opportunities for training and development</p><p>* A chance to be part of an exciting new restaurant opening</p>",
